{"article_id":"6S11n3sBXwFaYvBm","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Hurricane Florence ' s potentially devastating winds and rain could be like \" a Mike Tyson punch \"","depth":4},{"id":1,"text":"when the storm slams into the Carolina coast later this week .","depth":4},{"id":2,"text":"The hurricane ,","depth":9},{"id":3,"text":"which was downgraded to a Category 3 early Wednesday afterrnoon ,","depth":9},{"id":4,"text":"remains strong","depth":8},{"id":5,"text":"as it continues its approach to the U.S. Mid-Atlantic region with maximum sustained winds of 125 mph ,","depth":7},{"id":6,"text":"the National Hurricane Center said in its 2 p.m. advisory .","depth":6},{"id":7,"text":"Florence was 435 miles southeast of Wilmington , North Carolina ,","depth":8},{"id":8,"text":"and moving northwest at 16 mph .","depth":8},{"id":9,"text":"It 's expected to go back up to a Category 4 by Thursday morning .","depth":7},{"id":10,"text":"Steve Goldstein , FEMA 's National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration liaison , said Wednesday morning","depth":7},{"id":11,"text":"that the agency expected the storm to hit late Thursday or early Friday morning .","depth":7},{"id":12,"text":"Jeff Byard , associate administrator for the Office of Response and Recovery at the Federal Emergency Management Agency","depth":8},{"id":13,"text":"( FEMA ) ,","depth":8},{"id":14,"text":"urged residents in the mandatory evacuation zones across the region to pack up","depth":8},{"id":15,"text":"and leave the area sooner rather than later .","depth":8},{"id":16,"text":"\" It ' s a very dangerous storm -","depth":8},{"id":17,"text":"heed the warnings","depth":10},{"id":18,"text":"and evacuate","depth":10},{"id":19,"text":"if you are in one of those zones .","depth":9},{"id":20,"text":"Today is the day , \"","depth":8},{"id":21,"text":"he said Wednesday morning .","depth":8},{"id":22,"text":"\" This is going to be a Mike Tyson punch to the Carolina coast . \"","depth":6},{"id":23,"text":"According to Fox News Senior Meteorologist Janice Dean ,","depth":7},{"id":24,"text":"Florence could stall","depth":9},{"id":25,"text":"upon reaching the Carolina coast","depth":9},{"id":26,"text":"and make a slight shift south","depth":10},{"id":27,"text":"once it makes landfall ,","depth":10},{"id":28,"text":"becoming a \" major flooding event . \"","depth":9},{"id":29,"text":"HURRICANE FLORENCE COULD BRING CATASTROPHIC STORM SURGES :","depth":4},{"id":30,"text":"WHAT ARE THEY ,","depth":5},{"id":31,"text":"AND HOW CAN YOU PREPARE ?","depth":5},{"id":32,"text":"In addition to the hurricane-strength winds","depth":6},{"id":33,"text":"blowing ashore Friday ,","depth":6},{"id":34,"text":"Florence has the potential","depth":6},{"id":35,"text":"to bring a storm surge upwards of 6 feet in parts of the coastline","depth":7},{"id":36,"text":"including up to 13 feet from Cape Fear north to Cape Lookout .","depth":7},{"id":37,"text":"The hurricane could also produce heavy and excessive rainfall","depth":6},{"id":38,"text":"- up to 40 inches in isolated areas in the Carolinas and anywhere between 6 to 12 inches elsewhere in the Appalachians and Mid-Atlantic region .","depth":6},{"id":39,"text":"It will also pass directly over two nuclear power plants","depth":8},{"id":40,"text":"-- the Brunswick Nuclear Plant ,","depth":9},{"id":41,"text":"which is located 30 miles south of Wilmington ,","depth":9},{"id":42,"text":"as well as the Shearon Harris Nuclear Plant in New Hill , about 23 miles from Raleigh .","depth":7},{"id":43,"text":"Flooding well inland could wreck environmental havoc","depth":7},{"id":44,"text":"by washing over industrial waste sites and hog farms .","depth":7},{"id":45,"text":"HURRICANE FLORENCE EMERGENCY CONTACTS TO NOTE AS 'EXTREMELY DANGEROUS ' STORM HITS EAST COAST","depth":3},{"id":46,"text":"On Wednesday morning , President Trump urged caution to residents","depth":8},{"id":47,"text":"refusing to evacuate coastal towns ,","depth":8},{"id":48,"text":"saying","depth":8},{"id":49,"text":"Florence is \" bigger than anticipated . \"","depth":8},{"id":50,"text":"\" Hurricane Florence is looking bigger than anticipated , \"","depth":8},{"id":51,"text":"Trump tweeted .","depth":8},{"id":52,"text":"\" It will be arriving soon .","depth":8},{"id":53,"text":"FEMA , First Responders and Law Enforcement are supplied and ready .","depth":9},{"id":54,"text":"Be safe ! \"","depth":9},{"id":55,"text":"He then released a video","depth":7},{"id":56,"text":"urging residents in affected areas to \" get out of its way .","depth":7},{"id":57,"text":"\" Don ' t play games with it -","depth":7},{"id":58,"text":"it ' s a big one ,","depth":9},{"id":59,"text":"may be as big","depth":10},{"id":60,"text":"as they ' ve seen , \"","depth":10},{"id":61,"text":"Trump added .","depth":8},{"id":62,"text":"Earlier this week Trump declared states of emergency for North and South Carolina and Virginia ,","depth":6},{"id":63,"text":"opening the way for federal aid .","depth":6},{"id":64,"text":"All three states ordered mass evacuations along the coast .","depth":6},{"id":65,"text":"But getting out of harm ' s way has proved difficult .","depth":7},{"id":66,"text":"Local resident Michelle Stober loaded up valuables on Tuesday at her home on Wrightsville Beach","depth":11},{"id":67,"text":"to drive back to her primary residence in Cary , N.C.","depth":11},{"id":68,"text":"Finding fuel for the journey was tough .","depth":11},{"id":69,"text":"`` This morning I drove around for an hour","depth":14},{"id":70,"text":"looking for gas in Cary .","depth":14},{"id":71,"text":"Everyone was sold out , ''","depth":13},{"id":72,"text":"she said .","depth":12},{"id":73,"text":"People across the region rushed","depth":10},{"id":74,"text":"to buy bottled water and other supplies ,","depth":11},{"id":75,"text":"board up their homes ,","depth":12},{"id":76,"text":"pull their boats out of the water","depth":13},{"id":77,"text":"and get out of town .","depth":13},{"id":78,"text":"Long lines formed at service stations ,","depth":10},{"id":79,"text":"and some started running out of gas as far west as Raleigh , with bright yellow bags , signs or rags","depth":12},{"id":80,"text":"placed over the pumps","depth":12},{"id":81,"text":"to show","depth":12},{"id":82,"text":"they were out of order .","depth":12},{"id":83,"text":"Some store shelves were picked clean .","depth":10},{"id":84,"text":"`` There 's no water .","depth":12},{"id":85,"text":"There 's no juices .","depth":13},{"id":86,"text":"There 's no canned goods , ''","depth":13},{"id":87,"text":"Kristin Harrington said","depth":12},{"id":88,"text":"as she shopped at a Walmart in Wilmington .","depth":12},{"id":89,"text":"AS HURRICANE FLORENCE BARRELS TOWARD US ,","depth":4},{"id":90,"text":"'WORST CASE SCENARIO ' SIMULATION OF CATEGORY 4 STORM SHOWS CATASTROPHIC DEVASTATION","depth":4},{"id":91,"text":"Despite all that ,","depth":5},{"id":92,"text":"65-year-old Liz Browning Fox plans to ride the storm out in the Outer Banks village of Buxton , N.C. ,","depth":6},{"id":93,"text":"despite a mandatory evacuation order .","depth":6},{"id":94,"text":"Her 88-year-old mother refused to evacuate","depth":6},{"id":95,"text":"and will stay with her .","depth":6},{"id":96,"text":"`` Everyone","depth":8},{"id":97,"text":"who is staying here","depth":8},{"id":98,"text":"is either a real old-timer , someone","depth":9},{"id":99,"text":"who does n't know","depth":10},{"id":100,"text":"where would be better ,","depth":10},{"id":101,"text":"or someone","depth":9},{"id":102,"text":"involved in emergency operations one way or another , ''","depth":9},{"id":103,"text":"said Fox .","depth":6}],"relations":[{"parent":207,"left":148,"right":206,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":148,"left":132,"right":147,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":132,"left":105,"right":131,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":105,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":131,"left":114,